    <cdata>
      <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>&lt;pre&gt;[Congressional Record Volume 170, Number 107 (Wednesday, June 26, 2024)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [&lt;a href="https://www.gpo.gov"&gt;www.gpo.gov&lt;/a&gt;]By Mr. GOLDMAN of New York:H.R. 8842.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Under Article I, Section 8 of the Constitution, Congresshas the power ``to make all Laws which shall be necessary andproper for carrying into the Execution for the foregoingPowers, and all other Powers vested by this Constitution inthe Government of the United States, or any Department orOfficer thereof.''The single subject of this legislation is:A bill to ensure that the background check system used forfirearms purchases denies a firearm to a person prohibitedfrom possessing a firearm by a lawful court order governingthe pretrial release of the person.[Page H4321]&lt;/pre&gt;</constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
